align="left"><ul><li><strong>Authentication</strong>: This includes verifying identity to<br/> access applications and resources. It also includes providing <br/>functionality such as self-service password reset, multifactor <br/>authentication, a custom list of banned passwords, and smart lockout <br/>services.</li><li><strong>Single sign-on</strong>: Single sign-on (SSO) enables you to<br/> remember only one username and one password to access multiple <br/>applications. A single identity is tied to a user, which simplifies the <br/>security model. As users change roles or leave an organization, access <br/>modifications are tied to that identity, which greatly reduces the <br/>effort needed to change or disable accounts.</li><li><strong>Application management</strong>: You can manage your cloud <br/>and on-premises apps by using Microsoft Entra ID. Features like <br/>Application Proxy, SaaS apps, the My Apps portal, and single sign-on <br/>provide a better user experience.</li><li><strong>Device management</strong>: Along with accounts for <br/>individual people, Microsoft Entra ID supports the registration of <br/>devices. Registration enables devices to be managed through tools like <br/>Microsoft Intune. It also allows for device-based Conditional Access <br/>policies to restrict access attempts to only those coming from known <br/>devices, regardless of the requesting user account.</li></ul></div>" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="-1060" y="190" width="980" height="350" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="tHIQw-f0cl09mBN5cJ_6-15" value="<p>Microsoft Entra Domain Services is like a ready-made system that provides important features for managing computers and users in a network, without you having to set it up or maintain it yourself.</p><p>It helps you:</p><ul><li><strong>Connect computers to a network</strong> (domain join),</li><li><strong>Set rules for users and devices</strong> (group policy),</li><li><strong>Allow secure access to directories</strong> (LDAP),</li><li><strong>Handle secure logins</strong> (Kerberos/NTLM authentication).</li></ul><p>All of this works without you needing to worry about setting up or maintaining the servers (domain controllers) that usually provide these services. Microsoft takes care of all that for you in the cloud.</p>" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;resizable=0;points=[];autosize=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=11;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=default;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="-1070" y="230" width="980" height="160" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="tHIQw-f0cl09mBN5cJ_6-16" value="<h1 style="margin-top: 0px;"><br></h1><p>When you create a Microsoft Entra Domain Services managed domain, you <br/>define a unique namespace. This deployment of DCs is known as a replica set.</p>" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontSize=11;fontColor=default;labelBackgroundColor=default;" ul.li:
Authentication: This includes verifying identity to
access applications and resources. It also includes providing
functionality such as self-service password reset, multifactor
authentication, a custom list of banned passwords, and smart lockout
services.

Single sign-on: Single sign-on (SSO) enables you to
remember only one username and one password to access multiple
applications. A single identity is tied to a user, which simplifies the
security model. As users change roles or leave an organization, access
modifications are tied to that identity, which greatly reduces the
effort needed to change or disable accounts.

Application management: You can manage your cloud
and on-premises apps by using Microsoft Entra ID. Features like
Application Proxy, SaaS apps, the My Apps portal, and single sign-on
provide a better user experience.

Device management: Along with accounts for
individual people, Microsoft Entra ID supports the registration of
devices. Registration enables devices to be managed through tools like
Microsoft Intune. It also allows for device-based Conditional Access
policies to restrict access attempts to only those coming from known
devices, regardless of the requesting user account.

div.p: Microsoft Entra Domain Services is like a ready-made system that provides important features for managing computers and users in a network, without you having to set it up or maintain it yourself.

ul.li: Connect computers to a network (domain join),
Set rules for users and devices (group policy),
Allow secure access to directories (LDAP),
Handle secure logins (Kerberos/NTLM authentication).

div.p: All of this works without you needing to worry about setting up or maintaining the servers (domain controllers) that usually provide these services. Microsoft takes care of all that for you in the cloud.
